      "# ğŸ™ï¸ THE DUST SETTLES ON ROUND ONE! ğŸ™ï¸\n\n**This is Nok the Corrupter**, broadcasting LIVE from the wreckage of the First Round! The Playoffs have chewed up the weak and spit them out... but not quite *out* of the tournament! No, my friends, this is a **Double Elimination** gauntlet! \n\nThe winners stay in the sun-drenched **Winner's Bracket**, marching one step closer to the trophy. The losers? They don't go home to their mothers just yet. They are banished to the **Loser's Bracket**, a desperate, clawing pit where one more loss means EXTINCTION! \n\nLetâ€™s break down who stayed in the light and who fell into the shadow! ğŸ©¸ğŸ†\n\n---\n\n## âš”ï¸ THE GAME 3 DECIDERS: CLINGING TO THE WINNER'S BRACKET! âš”ï¸\n\nFive series went the absolute distance! These teams stared into the abyss of the Loser's Bracket and refused to blink!\n\n### ğŸ›¡ï¸ THE FORTRESS HOLDS: RUNEGUARD ADVANCE!\n**Game 3 Result: Kerlauger Runeguard 6 - New Prosperity Profits 5**\n\nBy the blackened pit, what a game! **The Kerlauger Runeguard** defended the Old Fort in a 6-5 thriller that saw more blood than a vampire's wedding! The Profits fought hardâ€”**Milman Galvan** even passed the ball to herself for a dunk!â€”but the Runeguardâ€™s **Harilda Sigsmond** and **Vivia Namara** turned the field into a graveyard. The Merchant Guildâ€™s gold couldn't buy a spot in the Winner's Bracket! The Runeguard stay up; the Profits fall down!\n\n### ğŸŒ² SILENCE IN THE SWAMP: OAK & ONSLAUGHT UPSET!\n**Game 3 Result: Oak & Onslaught 1 - Zmeigorod Snessengers 0**\n\nTHE BOG QUEEN WEEPS! The fan-favorite **Zmeigorod Snessengers** have been knocked down to the Loser's Bracket! **Oak & Onslaught** walked into the Serpent's Pass and delivered a defensive masterclass. The only point of the game came from **Millham Evangeline**, who caught a pass from Abner Seidel and dunked it home. The Snessengers tried to rally, but **Wynnie Faina** (wearing his boots on the wrong feet!) blocked everything in sight. The popular kids have to fight for their lives now! HA!\n\n### ğŸŒªï¸ CHAOS REIGNS: NARWHALS SINK!\n**Game 3 Result: New Monteforte Chaos Creatures 4 - Southport Narwhals 0**\n\nIt was a shutout at the Cliffside! The **New Monteforte Chaos Creatures** bulldozed the Southport Narwhals 4-0 to stay in the Winner's Bracket. **Placido Kora** launched a missile from Center Field, and **Mouldon Earl** added another 2-point beauty to seal the deal. The Narwhals couldn't handle the violence, with **Tucker Hett** turning into a one-woman wrecking crew. The Chaos Creatures advance; the Narwhals drop to the depths!\n\n### ğŸ•¯ï¸ HAVEN PREVAILS (UNFORTUNATELY)\n**Game 3 Result: Haven Lights 4 - Tortell Privateers 2**\n\nI hate to say it, but the **Haven Lights** are staying in the Winner's Bracket. They defeated the Tortell Privateers 4-2 at the Aegis Field. **Zwart Bunns** and **Farand Keil** hit big shots early, and despite a valiant effort (and lots of injuries) from the Privateers, the Shield held firm. **Dib Tufts** tried to turn it into a wrestling match, injuring two players, but the Lights survived. Gross. Go lose somewhere else, Privateers!\n\n### ğŸ­ THE CIRCUS ROLLS ON: BIZARRES WIN!\n**Game 3 Result: Starlight Bazaar Bizarres 4 - Wyrmwood Stronghammers 2**\n\nThe **Starlight Bazaar Bizarres** danced their way to victory in the Hollow Mine! **Pompei Hephzipa** and **Willa Lois** scored massive 2-point shots to silence the Stronghammers. Despite the home-field 'Humming Earth', Wyrmwood couldn't keep up with the Bizarres' flair. The Stronghammers are hammered down to the Loser's Bracket!\n\n---\n\n## ğŸ§¹ THE BROOMS: SWEEPING INTO THE NEXT ROUND! ğŸ§¹\n\nThree teams didn't even need a Game 3 (though they played one for fun/violence anyway)! They cruise into the next round of the Winner's Bracket while their opponents tumble into the pit!\n\n* **The Oread's Summit Tamers** swept **The Greenwatch** 2-0! A complete domination at high altitude! The Greenwatch falls to the Loser's Bracket to think about their life choices.\n* **The Confluence Captains** swept my **Ebon Gate Corruptors** 2-0. I don't want to talk about it. The Captains stay up. My boys go down to the Loser's Bracket where they can thrive in the muck.\n* **The New Ravenfall Commanders** swept **The South Pole Yetis** 2-0! The Yetis won the exhibition game, but it was too little, too late! The Commanders march on; the Yetis slide down the icy slope to the Loser's Bracket!\n\n---\n\n## ğŸ”® ROUND 2 IS COMING! ğŸ”®\n\nThe Winner's Bracket is full of killers! The Loser's Bracket is full of desperate animals! \n\nWho will stay undefeated? Who will claw their way back from the brink of elimination? The stakes have never been higher! Stay tuned, you maniacs! The playoffs are only getting hotter!\n\n**This is Nok the Corrupter, signing off! STAY VIOLENT!** ğŸ˜ˆ",
